<br>
Comparing druids to shamans is unfair because there is a strong argument that shamans are the most powerful class in the game.  Shamans are the masters of melee buffs, have the best slow in the game, have haste that is almost as good as an enchanter, have strong heals (thanks to changes made in the past year), have excellent DoTs, have fair nukes, have SoW, and (perhaps most importantly of all) have the ability to regenerate mana at a remarkable pace.  Druids aren't that strong, but so what?<br>
<br>
I've had the pleasure of grouping and raiding with some skilled druids in recent months.  I don't mean soloists who are slumming, I mean people who have actually taken the time to learn to play a druid in a group or as part of a raid.  News flash: druids do not suck.  They don't have one defining characteristic that they are better at than any other class, but they can do just about everything except melee.<br>
<br>
Do you need healing?  Druids do that just as well as shamans.  They can't CH like clerics, but you don't need CH for a lot of healing.  When I'm setting the groups on raids, I place the druids strategically because they are well equipped to heal non-tanks.  When I draw aggro because I just landed a CH on the main tank, and some nasty mob is trying to give me a normal-sized forehead again, who saves my ass?  It's usually the druid.  When you're using a CH rotation, and need some smaller heals to keep the tank alive, who does the job?  It's usually the druids.  When you're short on clerics, who do you fill the gaps with?  It's usually the druids.<br>
<br>
Do you need nuking?  Druids aren't as good as wizards or mages, but they have some pretty decent nukes.<br>
<br>
Do you need help with all of the ancillary spells?  Druids can SoW, lev, EB, invis, see invis, snare, DS, strengthen, regen, TP, root, etc. etc. etc.  And don't forget Circle of Winter and Circle of Summer, which are the best fire and cold resist spells in the game.<br>
<br>
Druids sometimes have a hard time finding a group because of all the dr00ds out there.  But people remember the capable druids who really know how to play the class well.<br>
<br>
